  "text": "Despite their increased brain activity, old subjects were still capable of parametrically modulating their BOLD response in paracingulate, bilateral premotor, and superior parietal areas. Similar findings have been observed in the context of motor control Ward et al. 2008b ). Moreover, [CITATION_1] have shown that failure to modulate brain activity may only become evident when substantial white matter hyperintensities, as measured by Fluid Attenuated Inversion Recovery, are present.",
